data.title: Willow/Bluff/Third Street Historic District
data.meta_description: The Willow/Bluff/Third Street district represents an early, intact residential neighborhood built by prospering, second generation merchants, railroad and real estate financiers, and professionals. Third Street was known as the “Street of Generals” because four men who attained the rank of general lived within a three-block area.
